Official Announcement on Use of Euro
BEIJING , December 28 ( Xinhua ) -- Financial institutions , enterprises and individuals in China can accept and use the euro in economic , trade and financial exchanges with 11 members of the European Union ( EU ) effective January 1 , 1999 .
The People 's Bank of China ( PBOC ) , the central bank , and the State Administration of Foreign Exchange ( SAFE ) made the joint announcement earlier today .
A SAFE spokesman outlined procedure for the three-year transition period from January 1 , 1999 to December 31 , 2001 .
He said Chinese institutions can either use the euro or the original currencies of European countries .
They will also have the option of using the Euro and original currencies simultaneously under the existing framework of foreign exchange administration laws .
In addition , they can convert , open and use the euro accounts in accordance with related regulations , according to the spokesman .
He noted that SAFE recently issued a circular on detailed matters concerning the administration of foreign exchange following introduction of the euro .
The unified European currency -- euro -- will be officially launched on January 1 , 1999 , in 11 member nations of the EU -- Belgium , Germany , Spain , France , Ireland , Italy , Luxembourg , the Netherlands , Austria , Portugal and Finland .
